President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has delegated certain functions and authorities to the Secretary of State under the Trans-Sahara Counterterrorism Partnership Program Act of 2022. The delegated provisions include section 104(b) regarding the Trans-Sahara Counterterrorism Partnership Program, section 104(d) regarding comprehensive 5-year strategies for counterterrorism efforts in the Sahel-Maghreb and the Trans-Sahara region, and section 104(f) regarding the submission of reports. The memorandum also authorizes and directs the publication of this delegation in the Federal Register.